olor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Unguilded Sexless Drood</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/10/01 11:39:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for all</span><hr size=1> Well as I think I told you the other day, I'm all for helping out.  Just give a time and I'll try to make it.  I've helped several other people with parts for their epics.  I think there is a simliar thread somewhere else on the board, I forget where (its that low int thing again).  <br><br>Just a few suggestions tho.  1) dont depend on CoG participation.  Try to get as many friends and guildmates as you can.  2)  Try to schedule it for a time that people can make it.  That is, during the late afternoons weekdsay or afternoons weekends US time.  And hope its not on the same day as some alliance raid.<br><br>Oh, just one other thing.  With a bit of work, you can do Ix multiple times.  So multiple clerics can get the item.  Bonus eh?<br><br>Kellory Silverstar<br>Crunchy! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufildiarsoulsaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fildiar Soulsaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/11/01 10:17:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for all</span><hr size=1> Thanks Kellory. And about us doing  Ix multiple times to get the piece, sounds great. Actually, after you kill  Ix is trigger won't spawn for 4 hours, so during that time we can zone into Chadok and kill the  Overking  (easier then  Ix, and spawns every  2 hours) sense we will have enough people. So  we can get the overking for the  clerics who need him a few  times before doing Ix again for  another cleric. Just a thought. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Unguilded Sexless Drood</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/11/01 11:43:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for all</span><hr size=1> Actually thats somewhat untrue, although I'm not sure if the method used to keep it's trigger around is an exploit or not.<br><br>The basics are that you keep the trigger hailed.  So long as someone is hailing it, I dont believe it will despawn.  I dont know if it needs to be charmed as well.  At least the last time I help about a month or two ago, we didi Ix about 4 or 5 times in a row.  I dont have all the info on it, I'd have to look it up.  But it is possible.  Or at least it was.  Hunting in Chardok also sounds good tho.  I need an SBS...<br><br>Kellory Silverstar<br>Crunchy! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufildiarsoulsaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fildiar Soulsaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/12/01 9:55:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for all</span><hr size=1> I was mislead when I  posted my post yesturday. From what I now know is that  once  you give  Naxot the piece I have, he will despawn instantly, and  Ix will spawn. But, at  6AM game time,  Naxot will respawn, so we will have like a 30-45  minute break time in between  killing Ix and Naxot re-spawn. So, yes if another cleric or  a few are at  this stage we could easily take and do this a few times. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udreamswalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DreamsWalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/12/01 12:06:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for all</span><hr size=1> Ill help I need the princes head from chardock for my epic ill keep checking back for a date. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukefo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kefo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/12/01 7:07:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for all</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't mind helping kill a epic mob and furthuring a cleric to their dream. If afterwards the ppl there decide to goto chardok I join in as well.....mabye the iksar betrayer will be up and I can actually start my epic. I'll check the boards for a date and time or just look for me online<br><br>Kefo<br>51 monk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufayen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fayen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/13/01 1:27:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for all</span><hr size=1> Hey, I guess I would be up for helping.  If I am on.  There is a piece that drops in Chardok for the mage epic, according to everlore.  It says the mob is level 55-60, not sure if we would have the fighting power to take it down, probably not, but anyway, i would be up for that afterwards if we were to head there.<br><br>Also, I was wondering if Kerra Ridge is worth going to, and if so, would many people be up for going there?  I know a piece for the wizard epic drops there, along with a lot of other stuff.  I have never been and been reading up on it, and it sounded like a cool place to visit.  <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukaltorsoulweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaltor Soulweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/13/01 12:20:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for all</span><hr size=1> Keep  someone hailing the trigger to keep him up...and so ya know the overking is much harder he melees for less but has much worse ae and is a caster and has upto 6 guards all very nasty with the chance of CH and aggro of the (god forbid)queen and herbalist, the ixiblat fer is actually a warrior med to low magic resist for his level so get  some wizards and his ae is a proc not a spell so chain runeV and nuke away and keep fire resist high.<br><br>Kaltor Soulweaver <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umaladamukheartmender.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladamuk Heartmender</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/18/01 3:31:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for all</span><hr size=1> You can no longer keep the turn-in NPC for Ixi from despawning, so you'll have to wait for respawn between fights - no more than 90 minutes.  That's a somewhat recent patch change.<br><br>Ixi is level 63, 32k hp, no noticeable immunities to spells.  Bring *both* magic and fire resist gear; recent reports indicate that the proc is an AoE MAGIC attack, rather than fire as previously believed.<br><br>Overking's biggest problem is his spells - he likes gravity flux which can aggro other things.  He also gates and can summon, which is a nasty combination if he gates to someplace where you can't see him.  His AoE is definitely fire-based.<br><br>There are lots of epic pieces that drop off the high-level targets in Chardok, so a raid there can be extremely productive from an epic perspective.  The Herbalist, the Prince, and the Overking are good big targets; the Queen, on the other hand, casts an unresistable AoE attack -- if ye aggro her, I hope ye've got a cleric camped <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br> <p>Maladamuk Heartmender<BR>Gnomish Vicar of the 53rd Ring<BR>Storm's Justice</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=r